No worries! You don't have to declare your major until the second semester of your sophomore year. You have plenty of time to explore and figure out what you'd like to concentrate on. The best thing you can do is sign up for a class or two within a subject you like or think you might like. This is a good way to see if you want to further pursuit classes within the department. Also, make sure to take classes outside of your comfort zones as you might find something new you love! The next step is to look at the availability of classes. That's great! You don't have to declare your major until the second semester of your sophomore year. The best thing you can do is sign up for a class or two within your expected major. This is a good way to ensure that you want to further pursue your intended major. Also, make sure to take classes outside of your "planned" major(s) as you might find something new you love! The next step is to look at the availability of classes. Have you looked at the spring class schedule yet? That's great! You don't have to declare your major until the second semester of your sophomore year. The best thing you can do is sign up for a class or two within your expected major. Make sure to also take classes outside of your "planned" majors as you might find something new you love! The next step is to look at the availability of classes. Have you looked at the spring class schedule yet? This will come in handy come registration time. When your registration period begins you will want to quickly select your desired courses as soon as possible. That will be your next step during registration. Creating a plan in 1600 Grand is a vital tool come registration time. When your registration period begins you will want to quickly select your desired courses as soon as possible. You're nearly ready for registration! Let's consider a few other things you should do consider: As a first year, you will most likely be registering last. This means that many of the classes you want to get into will most likely be filled. Do not fret! Here's what you can do: - Be flexible - Have plenty of backup options - Get on the class waiting list as soon as possible Even if you are not sure if the class will fill up it is better to be on a waiting list earlier rather than later. How to make a plan in 1600 Grand: 1. Go to 1600 Grand. 2. Under the student tab click on the "Enter registration" button. 3. Then select the "Plan Ahead" link. 4. Clicking on this link will prompt you to select the term you are preparing for (**please note that you might get an error message if it is too early to being with this process**). 5. Search for your classes and add them to your plan! [[How to prepare for registration]]Great! Make sure to check in with your advisor for your "registration PIN" and find your registration time (as of 10.17.2022 these times are not up). Now you are ready to begin looking into courses. A great place to start is through your major or prospective major. Do you have a major? [[Yes, I have a major!]] [[No, I don't have any idea yet]] [[I have ideas, but I am not sure yet]]First, you will receive a registration period in which you can sign up for next semester's classes. The times for 2023 registration have not been uploaded yet (as of 10.17.2022). To registrate for classes you need to get your "registration PIN" from your advisor (**in some special circumstances you may need to receive this from disability services**). Now you are ready to begin looking into courses. A great place to start is through your major or prospective major. Do you have a major?
